cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper focuses on local unsupervised learning for image analysis, specifically on designing a local algorithm for learning convolutional filters at scale on large image datasets. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of patch normalization and non-linearities, which are techniques commonly used in neural networks and machine learning, indicating a possible connection to the neural networks (cs.NE), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the classification accuracy of the learned filters, suggesting a possible connection to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category, which often deals with classification tasks.
